define({"topics":[{"title":"How do I display contacts with their full names or short names?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">On your contact list, you can display contacts’ full names (names with their server addresses) or short names (names without their server addresses). By default, full names are displayed.<\/p>","href":"t_entry_uim_contacts_shortfull_names.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_entry_uim_contacts_shortfull_names"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_entry_uim_contacts_shortfull_names-d433e204","topics":[]},{"title":"What ways can I display my Primary Contacts and other views?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">Use Primary Contacts to build a personalized list of contacts. Click <img class=\"image\" src=\"images\/ST_left_primary_inactive.JPG\" alt=\"Primary Contacts icon\"\/> to open the Primary Contacts list view, which can be customized with several different lists and view types.<\/p>","href":"t_st8_uim_views.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_st8_uim_views"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_st8_uim_views-d433e215","topics":[]},{"title":"How do I display contacts with their full names or short names?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">On your contact list, you can display contacts’ full names (names with their server addresses) or short names (names without their server addresses). By default, full names are displayed.<\/p>","href":"t_entry_uim_contacts_shortfull_names_2.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_entry_uim_contacts_shortfull_names"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_entry_uim_contacts_shortfull_names-d433e232","topics":[]},{"title":"How do I import a Sametime® contact list?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can import an HCL Sametime® contact list as a way to quickly add   a large number of contacts to your existing contact list. Or, you can import a pre-populated   contact list, if you don't already have one, or replace your existing contact list with the   names you import.<\/p>","href":"t_st852_uim_import_contact_list.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_st852_uim_import_contact_list"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_st852_uim_import_contact_list-d433e243","topics":[]},{"title":"How do I export my contact list?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can export the HCL Sametime® contacts from one or all of your   server communities to a file. You might export contacts if you want to save a local copy of your   contact list as backup. Or, other users can import the file so that they do not need to create   their own list of contacts. <\/p>","href":"t_st852_uim_export_contact_list.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_st852_uim_export_contact_list"},"menu":{"hasChildren":false},"tocID":"t_st852_uim_export_contact_list-d433e260","topics":[]},{"title":"How can I control how others see me in their contact list and who can contact me?","shortdesc":"<p class=\"shortdesc\">You can create privacy lists to control who sees your status on their contact list when you are online or when your status is \"Do Not Disturb.\" These lists apply to all your server communities. If you have access to external communities, you can set who can chat with you from those communities. See the following topics to learn more about setting your privacy preferences.<\/p>","href":"t_st8_uim_privacy.html","attributes":{"data-id":"t_st8_uim_privacy"},"menu":{"hasChildren":true},"tocID":"t_st8_uim_privacy-d433e274","next":"t_st8_uim_privacy-d433e274"}]});